1. Name the file and place it within its respective component folder. For this example, we will be placing it in the recpie directory
and naming the file recpie.model.ts. Below is the code for the model.

// If we wish to utuilize the model we must export it. 
export class Recipe {
  // Declare our fields. 
  public name: string;
  public description: string;
  public imagePath: string;
 // use a contructor to initialize the fields, this may not be neccesarry with dynamic data.
  constructor(name: string, description: string, imagePath: string) {
    this.name = name;
    this.description = description;
    this.imagePath = imagePath;
  }
}


2. Now we will head over to out recpies-list.ts file and import the model we created.

import { Component, OnInit } from '@angular/core';
// Notice how we must prefix the file pathe of import with ".." this is to ensure that we move out of the current directory and head 
to the correct directory which is holding our model. 
import { Recipe } from '../recipe.model';
@Component({
  selector: 'app-recipes-list',
  templateUrl: './recipes-list.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./recipes-list.component.css']
})
export class RecipesListComponent implements OnInit {
  // We now create a recipes field and make it of type Recipe model array. Sice we utuilized a constructor in the model file, we can
  input static data here and call it in the template using string interplation. 
  recipes: Recipe[] = [
    new Recipe('German', 'german recipe', 'https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2017/06/21/22/42/recipe-2428926_960_720.jpg')
  ] ;
  constructor() { }
  ngOnInit() {
  }
}

3. Below we use string interpelation to display our data from the ts file
    // Notice how we must use ngFor in the anchor tag so that the recpie data can be displayed.
    <a href="#" class="list-group-item clearfix" *ngFor="let recipe of recipes">
        <div class="pull-left">
            <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">{{recipe.name}}</h4>
            <p class="list-group-item-text">{{recipe.description}}</p>
        </div>
        <span class="pull-right">
          <img src="{{recipe.imagePath}}" alt="" class="img-responisve" style="max-height: 50px;">
        </span>
      </a>
